text: Sinoutskerke en Baarsdorp is a former municipality in the Dutch province of Zeeland. It existed until 1816, when it was merged with 's-Heer Abtskerke. As its name implies, the municipality It covered two hamlets, Sinoutskerke and Baarsdorp, located west and northwest of 's-Heer Abtskerke. There is also a Lordship of Sinoutskerke and Baarsdorp, owned by the van Huykelom van de Pas family.https://www.sinoutskerkebaarsdorp.nl/en ==References== Category:Former municipalities of Zeeland Category:Borsele
